   <abstract>A black and white photograph of Alfred Jackson&apos;s son Gus with two  yet to be indentified descendents of Alfred in the south room of Alfred&apos;s Cabin.  Gus is seated in a rocking chair at left while a younger woman sits in a chair to the right with a young child standing next to her.  Shows four poster bed in SE corner, rocking chair, two tables, trunk, chest, water cooler.  A clock and lamp also appear in the picture.  Image is mounted to grey cardboard with a black stripe around the image.  &quot;Thuss/Nashville, Tenn&quot; is imbossed on the lower left hand corner of the print.</abstract>
